# --- Required -----------------------------------------------------------------

# From @BotFather.
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABC...

# Comma-separated Telegram user IDs (get yours from @userinfobot). Anyone not
# listed is ignored. Everyone listed can approve tool calls — i.e. run commands
# on this machine. The broker refuses to start if this is empty.
TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_USERS=123456789

# Required for the topic-per-session workflow: the forum-enabled group where /new
# opens one topic per session. Omit it only for the degraded mode — a DM with the
# bot, one session for the whole chat.
#
# To find the id: start the broker and send /help in the group. The log line
# `[telegram] from <you> chat=-100... topic=...` carries it.
TELEGRAM_GROUP_ID=-1001234567890

# --- Optional -----------------------------------------------------------------

# Directory a session starts in when /new is given no path.
# Default: your home directory.
BROKER_DEFAULT_CWD=/storage/Work

# Where the conversation -> session-id registry is written.
# Default: ~/.claude-telegram-broker.json
BROKER_STATE_FILE=/home/you/.claude-telegram-broker.json

# Where /watch leaves messages for a watched session to pick up (one
# subdirectory per session id), and where that session leaves the questions it
# wants answered. The broker, the poller armed inside the watched session and the
# AskUserQuestion hook must all agree on this — change it for all three or none.
# Default: ~/.claude/telegram_mirror
# BROKER_MIRROR_DIR=/home/you/.claude/telegram_mirror

# Model for spawned sessions. Default: whatever the Agent SDK picks.
BROKER_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# Baseline behaviour for tools NOT listed in BROKER_ASK_TOOLS:
#   default            standard rules; unmatched tools run without a prompt
#   acceptEdits        auto-accept file edits
#   plan               explore only, no edits
#   bypassPermissions  skip all checks (BROKER_ASK_TOOLS still prompts)
# Default: default
BROKER_PERMISSION_MODE=default

# Tools that ALWAYS require an Allow/Deny confirmation in Telegram. This is what
# actually enforces the gate — read the Security section before shortening it.
# Default: Bash,Write,Edit,NotebookEdit
BROKER_ASK_TOOLS=Bash,Write,Edit,NotebookEdit

# How long a multiple-choice question from Claude (AskUserQuestion) waits for you
# to tap an option before falling back — in a watched session it goes up in that
# session's own UI, in a brokered one Claude proceeds on its best judgement.
# Ten minutes, because the whole point is that you are not at the keyboard.
# Change it and re-run `pnpm run print-hooks`: the hook's `timeout` in
# settings.json is derived from this and has to stay above it.
# Default: 600
# BROKER_ASK_TIMEOUT_SEC=600

# --- Voice notes (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
#
# Claude cannot hear audio — the API takes text, images and PDFs — so a voice
# note is only useful once something transcribes it. That something is a local
# whisper.cpp, and it is off until you point this at one.
#
# Local rather than a speech API on purpose: a hosted transcriber would put a
# third party you didn't choose in front of your microphone, for every voice
# note. See PRIVACY.md. Leave this unset and voice notes are declined, never
# sent anywhere.
#
# Directory holding the whisper.cpp binary (whisper-cli, or main on older
# builds) and a ggml-*.bin model. See the README for what to install and where
# from. Default: unset — audio off.
# BROKER_WHISPER_DIR=/opt/whisper

# Which model to use, when you keep several in that directory. Named but absent
# is an error, not a quiet fallback to a different model.
# Default: the first ggml-*.bin found, sorted.
# BROKER_WHISPER_MODEL=ggml-large-v3-turbo.bin

# Spoken-language hint. 'auto' detects per message; naming the language is a
# little faster and more accurate if you always speak the same one.
# Default: auto
# BROKER_WHISPER_LANGUAGE=es
